<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-185DB046-BA15-4640-9F1D-42559AD933C5" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-185DB046-BA15-4640-9F1D-42559AD933C5" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">05 How to remove the optical fiber cable</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-0E3E2CA2-5349-4FAF-80F5-347AA9765351"><p class="- topic/p ">This document describes how to remove the optical fiber cable between the carriage unit and the controller. 
</p><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-AE97ABB1-01A0-4BC8-BA2D-9D851A6C4D1B" type="important"><p class="- topic/p ">The fiber ends of the fiber cable are sensitive for contamination (dust) or scratches. 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Use the protection caps</b>. 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="FIG_5513EC4AB4474633A64B06BC0E7B4D87"><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-01DBD0D9-F9B2-4E4C-BFD0-D1B408097401-low.png" id="IMAGE_4FCA66C485254EF1BA90600FA63C6461" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-01DBD0D9-F9B2-4E4C-BFD0-D1B408097401-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">When the fiber protection caps are removed connect the connector immediately. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The bend radius of the cable is 60 mm during handling and 40 mm when installed. 
</p></note></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Dis-assembly</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-F8EE43B1-36AF-4F86-8810-3B686A03AF19" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li id="LI_53184B16D403439F881DA2AB90C20E0F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Go to COLD SDS and disconnect the Service jumper. 
</p></li><li id="LI_E38C1631665D4BE69728BB4374F0432B" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the top cover. 
</p><note type="important" id="GUID-7215619B-4D8E-42B1-B219-10C1EF6B5FB5" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not lean on the strip support. 
</p></note></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the cover of the carriage unit. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="05DISA002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-F9FDA7D9-BA95-4871-8DF6-98726C3BC391.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 05 How to remove the cover of the carriage unit...?>05 How to open the cover of the carriage unit</xref> 
</p></li><li id="LI_C54EF666B39942F0ABB7E4C12DDF80BA" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the metal strip. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="05DISA044" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-53D4F91E-5AFE-4299-AE69-C14CC7C9FDA3.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 05 How to remove the metal strip?>05 How to remove the strip support (metal strip)</xref> 
</p></li><li id="LI_316D4E0C25FB46B4A2116B36309DF3E9" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the ink system . 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="02DISA012" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-1C874C66-3A17-4AC4-886B-753A1A37D196.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 02 Open the ink system?>02 Open the ink system</xref> 
</p></li></ol></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_E753369EFDC5426BBE20201BB8995B3D" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_817B42AA77184C32836CE70E1B0DBB6C" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Cleaning material. 
</p></li><li id="LI_2AA4C5033A104BD390424FEF9FB7401E" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Small screwdriver. 
</p></li><li id="LI_67247CE54317489BBC59527BD3ED3160" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20. 
</p></li><li id="LI_4E0A2AAC80784F19B97EBA24BE695E98" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Side cutter. 
</p></li><li id="LI_ED521866AD8044239B500EB5B900D6E8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">4 Protection caps. 
</p></li><li id="LI_929C0F12811B4096BB70DA320BD9C6C8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Protective gloves: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Microflex</b> 93-260 gloves. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-DB340B14-87E5-4FDB-8108-245D16C84FF1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="FIG_6F2CF62E38854A52B6DC7E2C11FBE9A4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-AE194AB7-5F2D-4C54-B795-A84B4119A4C3-low.png" id="IMAGE_AD434179B3474FF6BD4702B394A7C0D2" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AE194AB7-5F2D-4C54-B795-A84B4119A4C3-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_A7FFC9665B2F4122AF27A06C7CBEF297" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Preparation</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_E42E6CC46B364362BF8288430C4E612A" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Place a sheet of media on the platen. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_7AE29DE6AF2846C9994AC349161FE88D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-028128CA-1927-4C78-BBA1-E88638D0F3A2-low.png" id="IMAGE_7D64AC53225241D3A33A3A9F9C28DB82" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-028128CA-1927-4C78-BBA1-E88638D0F3A2-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the manual maintenance door and place a paper towel. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_59E9C68B229443EBB7001CC44236041D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BCF78FE4-D02E-415C-9A19-E9CA438B17FA-low.png" id="IMAGE_0963BDA3AA13454BAE60527E5FFF4DF1" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BCF78FE4-D02E-415C-9A19-E9CA438B17FA-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Guide the printhead carriage to the left hand side of the system. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_43279F846E9D429688701088B155D466" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-3D6247F6-CC27-40D0-A573-4C029C78B2DA-low.png" id="IMAGE_A103BD4CBE5A4FC8A1A97C18094147F3" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-3D6247F6-CC27-40D0-A573-4C029C78B2DA-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Guide the UV lamp carriage to the middle. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_E951821F695643FD919836750E28E2F0" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-ECE3646D-FB56-4833-B155-AC2A729C837F-low.png" id="IMAGE_E9716AFC70894839A27DAB33C7CEF4CE" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-ECE3646D-FB56-4833-B155-AC2A729C837F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="SECTION_7BCF39D178844448B3A21E7E56376710" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to remove</title><table id="TABLE_5FBEFB7447DE4A1D819BDF873A72E3DB" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Disconnect the optical fiber connector 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Place 2 protection caps on the glass fibers. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_2E2EC23BB60A442DB9AB92EB83D4BA11" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-AE194AB7-5F2D-4C54-B795-A84B4119A4C3-low.png" id="IMAGE_8385BE61A3B640348DB9290C67A05CB2" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AE194AB7-5F2D-4C54-B795-A84B4119A4C3-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the glass fiber cable from the printhead carriage. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_030866CC428E4997AF72449221736874" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BC789C50-0071-44C2-BDCA-20A78D41D661-low.png" id="IMAGE_AF68A80B435B42FDAB6279FACEBC3165" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BC789C50-0071-44C2-BDCA-20A78D41D661-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the cover (3 screws). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_5D4073A9522B461F95A4DF40D0695E9D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F8E73780-FF3D-4E83-9867-2132546B1332-low.png" id="IMAGE_AAF593FD610746DC8ED9A5A361D45391" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F8E73780-FF3D-4E83-9867-2132546B1332-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_A5CDB800BB47456FB6E1BF14D94018EC" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5F8E28CB-A0D0-4ABC-BC40-9FBF277D14DE-low.png" id="IMAGE_145B6DF54FC2409387A2083FEF581100" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5F8E28CB-A0D0-4ABC-BC40-9FBF277D14DE-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove 1 screw of the locking strip of the tubes and cable and loosen the other side. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_8848CCB9E62140CAA243098306707819" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-82E8250A-0768-4ACF-8755-A12F7CF82EB0-low.png" id="IMAGE_73DEAF5831F4407CBC7A9FC1BC08C839" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-82E8250A-0768-4ACF-8755-A12F7CF82EB0-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Turn the locking strip away. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_461671BFCCE0408EA4EEF8A1B4F61E88" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5F64D8A3-BD97-49C8-8759-6BE73FD340A1-low.png" id="IMAGE_1A3E1E78C3D84A57806BA56E3D9765FB" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5F64D8A3-BD97-49C8-8759-6BE73FD340A1-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the clip of the holder. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_EAEC6A37522C4F65AAD31C59B8A0AF1D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6ECF1261-1B31-426B-8A84-85A773684F4D-low.png" id="IMAGE_3B01D406497C4AF1A094AFB075F34788" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6ECF1261-1B31-426B-8A84-85A773684F4D-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_475E065AC2144CE299FCAEA3D26B0A59" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-09A16186-8887-49B4-8C7F-DA968A2F3B51-low.png" id="IMAGE_55864C8A2F6D4B7E83A6DAB734A837DA" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-09A16186-8887-49B4-8C7F-DA968A2F3B51-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the required fiber cable (mark the position). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_9A7FDF82638F4DEF879B9D2545C4893A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-16CD05F6-CB79-4ADD-AD87-0C7C3CFD5637-low.png" id="IMAGE_F828463756824208A25E4942BB8B335F" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-16CD05F6-CB79-4ADD-AD87-0C7C3CFD5637-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the guide strip. (Slide it out of the melinex strip). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_A8E27B6788194DFB958F0A030E130B6E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-1F09E497-9C8A-475B-B353-224F4EA47157-low.png" id="IMAGE_46E6C569301A495F9C500B125DC27F8F" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-1F09E497-9C8A-475B-B353-224F4EA47157-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_56CFEFE999C04D9FA9D4AFB67EE96B6A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-90ADF53A-EF3D-4FD7-875F-85259EE00268-low.png" id="IMAGE_901AC00DB15B4F758CA3F7A06464F8C3" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-90ADF53A-EF3D-4FD7-875F-85259EE00268-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Repeat these actions for the other clips and guide strips. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_5F98CA0FDB6E45DF818531B9E3023AA0" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-CCA405ED-79CB-4FA1-926D-FD96BFF41213-low.png" id="IMAGE_051E5884015245429B374F38DA1B4990" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CCA405ED-79CB-4FA1-926D-FD96BFF41213-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the bracket (2 screws). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_A93E0A20A3F04AC496991950AB2C2E07" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-606FC6FF-AFEE-4215-86FC-A9C2BDC6275C-low.png" id="IMAGE_3EB8E39697794BAB9AEC96C187F5222A" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-606FC6FF-AFEE-4215-86FC-A9C2BDC6275C-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">12 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the guide strips: slide them out of the melinex strip. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_BFFC51B1CADB42E9A58EA603DF915035" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6F3392A7-9D84-412E-82A3-105437A65AD1-low.png" id="IMAGE_4EEA4B81B53F41BD82E4452BDACDDF80" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6F3392A7-9D84-412E-82A3-105437A65AD1-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">13 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Cut the 3 cable ties. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_2A1612F3FF8E49DB860F13746919CE8A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-25A4FFF2-A615-4F9E-A4DD-D3D1B1AD5541-low.png" id="IMAGE_1B3DDDCA42BE46929556CF894204AB0F" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-25A4FFF2-A615-4F9E-A4DD-D3D1B1AD5541-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_C4E4AE03CF9F48D5BF9E524339D4A6CF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A380DF78-1C73-40E8-9421-9970CDAF8ED3-low.png" id="IMAGE_FCE67842490B46C09DFE5AF463BD6C7B" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A380DF78-1C73-40E8-9421-9970CDAF8ED3-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">14 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the media input cover. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">15 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the guide plate (2 screws). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_DB522C75BE6B469387C4D64F590D6CD7" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-807BBD01-2C76-42DF-A248-B100A8E2FF41-low.png" id="IMAGE_4346669764324DDFA3AF940D74FC8D73" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-807BBD01-2C76-42DF-A248-B100A8E2FF41-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">16 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the cable guides and remove the optical fiber cable. 
